quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  72,20,"Say (O Muhammad): “I only pray to my Lord, and I associate none as partners with Him.”"
  72,21,"Say: “Surely I don’t have power to cause you harm, nor bring you the Right Way.”"
  72,22,"Say (O Muhammad): “(If I were to disobey Him) none can protect me from Allah’s punishment, nor can I find refuge except in Him"
  72,23,"(My mission is) only to convey the truth from Allah and His Messages. Those who disobey Allah and His Messenger, then surely, they will be put in the fire of hell to reside in it forever.”"
  72,24,"Till, when they will see (the punishment) that which they are Promised, then they will know whose helpers are weak and whose (supporters) are less in numbers"
  72,25,"Say (O Muhammad): “I don’t know whether (punishment) which you are Promised is near or whether my Lord has appointed for it a distant term"
  72,26,"(He alone is) the All-Knower of the unseen, and He does not reveal His unseen to anyone"
  72,27,except to the Messenger whom He has chosen. Then He makes a band of watching guards (angels) to march before him and behind him
  72,28,so that He may know that surely they (the Messengers) have conveyed the messages of their Lord. And He surrounds all their surroundings and He keeps a count of all things.”